[[File:Lahore Gymkhana.2.jpg|thumb|right|350px]]
The '''Lahore Gymkhana Club''' is a social and sports club in [[Lahore]], [[Pakistan]]. It offers sports facilities, including golf, swimming, cricket and squash, and organizes social activities for the members. It is situated on Upper Mall Road or Shahrah-e-Quaid-e-Azam.<ref>[http://www.pakistangolffederation.org/pages/clubs.aspx?c_id=9 In the list of Pakistan Golf Federation]</ref>

Established on 1st May, 1878, Lahore Gymkhana was formed to provide social recreation, and sports facilities to the residents of Lahore city and cantonment. The Club is spread over land, measuring {{convert|117.03|acre|km2}}, leased from Punjab Government. 

After independence of Pakistan, the management of the club was taken over by native residents. It is presently managed by a committee of elected members.

The Lahore Gymkhana has the following facilities available for its members: golf course, tennis courts, squash courts, swimming pools, cricket ground, billiard room and gym. It also frequently organizes concerts, lectures, and seminars.

